'''Amedia AS''' is one of the three largest [[media company|media companies]] in [[Norway]] (the other two are [[Schibsted]] and [[Polaris Media]]) and was established on May 27, 1948 with the name '''Norsk Arbeiderpresse''' (lit: ''Norwegian Labour Press''). It took the name '''A-pressen''' in 1994, which it retained until 2012. Amedia is whole or partial owner of 50 local- and regional [[newspaper]] with [[online newspapers]] and [[printing press]]es, local [[TV channel]]s and local [[radio channel]]s, including a 50% ownership of [[TV2 Group|TV2]] and its own [[news agency]], [[Avisenes Nyhetsbyr<U+00E5>]]. The corporation also owns and operates a group of printing plants under the brand name [[Prime Print]] in [[Russia]]. 

==History==
The company was originally created to finance the Norwegian [[labour newspaper]]s owned by the [[labour union]]s and [[Norwegian Labour Party|Labour Party]]. In 1990 the company was [[refinancing|refinanced]] and transferred to a [[corporation]] with the [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions]] and the Labour Party as the largest owners. When A-pressen bough part of TV2 the Labour Party chose to sell their ownership in the company, and instead the [[M<U+00F8>llerGruppen]], Finnish [[Sanoma]] and [[Telenor]] bought part of the company and it was listed on the [[Oslo Stock Exchange]]. In the end Sanoma sold their stocks, the company was delisted and it is now owned by the [[Norwegian Confederation of Trade Unions]] (45.2%), [[Telenor]] (44.8%) and the [[Fritt Ord (organization)|Fritt Ord Foundation]] (10.1%).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.medieregisteret.no/database/dbprogs/?1=1&eid=2832 |title=A-pressen AS |author=[[Medietilsynet]] |language=Norwegian |accessdate=28 January 2007 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20061212002359/http://www.medieregisteret.no/database/dbprogs/?1=1&eid=2832 |archivedate = 12 December 2006}}</ref> The company bought [[Edda Media]] in 2011.

The company has had five CEOs, [[Johan Ona]] (1948<U+2013>1974), [[Einar Olsen (editor)|Einar Olsen]] (1974<U+2013>1987), [[Alf Hildrum]] (1987<U+2013>2007), [[Even Nordstr<U+00F8>m]] (2007<U+2013>2010), and [[Thor Gjermund Eriksen]] (2010-present).

Chairmen of the board have been [[Konrad Nordahl]] (1948<U+2013>1965),<ref>{{stortingetbio|KONO|name=Konrad Nordahl}}</ref> [[Tor Aspengren]] (1965<U+2013>1981),<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Tor Aspengren|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Tor_Aspengren|language=Norwegian|accessdate=27 May 2010}}</ref> [[Tor Halvorsen]] (1981?<U+2013>1987), [[Leif Haraldseth]] (1987<U+2013>1990, acting from 1987 to 1988), [[Svein-Erik Oxholm]] (1990<U+2013>1997), [[Jan Balstad]] (1997<U+2013>2002), [[Roar Fl<U+00E5>then]] (2002<U+2013>2005), [[Gerd-Liv Valla]] (2005<U+2013>2007), [[Erik Nord]] (2007<U+2013>2010) and [[Jon Hippe]] (2010-present).

